HEADWORD: Refulgent
<hw>Re*ful"gent</hw> <pr>(r?*f?l"j⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>refulgens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>refulgere</ets> to flash back, to
shine bright; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>fulgere</ets> to shine.
See <er>Fulgent</er>.]</ety> <def>Casting a bright light; radiant;
brilliant; resplendent; shining; splendid; <as>as, <ex>refulgent</ex>
beams</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Re*ful"gent*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So conspicuous and <qex>refulgent</qex> a truth.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refund</ent>⟦br⟧
